<item>
 <title>Ambush in Mogadishu</title>
 <link>https://kennedyprize.columbia.edu/winners/2013/obrien/page/ambush-mogadishu</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-featured-image field-type-image field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;panopoly-image-half&quot; src=&quot;https://kennedyprize.columbia.edu/winners/2013/obrien/sites/default/files/styles/panopoly_image_half/public/pages/Screen%20Shot%202013-12-06%20at%203.42.14%20PM.png?itok=6mOd_oNq&quot; width=&quot;480&quot; height=&quot;318&quot; /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;A &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.pbs.org/wgbh/pages/frontline/shows/ambush/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;supplemental website&lt;/a&gt; to the 1995 PBS &quot;Frontline&quot; documentary &quot;Ambush in Mogadishu,&quot; including a historical timeline of the battle, an interactive map of the firefight, teachers&#039; guides, related readings, and a transcript of the documentary. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&quot;&#039;Frontline&#039; offers a tour de force tonight. Short on pictures of the October 1993 firefight in the Somali capital, &#039;Ambush in Mogadishu&#039; provides a compelling account through the memories of United States Army Rangers who found themselves pinned down for 17 hours. Eighteen Americans were killed - the most memorable picture was of a body being dragged through the streets - and scores more wounded, with enduring consequences for American foreign policy.&quot; - Walter Goodman, &lt;em&gt;New York Times&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.pbs.org/wgbh/pages/frontline/shows/ambush/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Ambush in Mogadishu | PBS Frontline&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
